  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. Domestic Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Proceeds of Crime legislation\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Provisions\n- Criminalization of money laundering activities\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Financial institution compliance requirements\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement investigations\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Civil penalty systems\n\n5. Regulatory Compliance\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Risk assessment procedures\n- Reporting obligations\n\n6. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing between jurisdictions\n- Extradition agreements\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n\nThe specific details can vary by country, but these elements generally form the core of money laundering legal frameworks.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these aspects?",
